      <title>Suspect held after attempted suicide attack in New York</title>
      <description><![CDATA[Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com or contact inquiries@nextanimation.com.tw to license this or any News Direct videoFor story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twRESTRICTIONS: NONEA Bangladeshi man set off a homemade explosive device in one of Manhattan's busiest transit hubs, in what authorities are calling a terrorist attack.According to the New York Times,the incident occurred in the underground passageway between the Port Authority Times Square subway stations.27-year-old suspect Akayed Ullah had strapped a pipe bomb to his body using velcro and zip ties, and detonated the device around 7:20 a.m.The powder-filled pipe was ignited using a Christmas light bulb, matches, and a 9-volt battery, but failed to detonate properly. One cap was blown off, but the rest of the pipe remained intact.Ullah sustained burns and lacerations to his hands and abdomen, and was taken to the hospital after being subdued by police. Several others received minor injuries.The suspect claimed the bombing was done in retaliation to U.S. airstrikes on the Islamic State in Syria, and says he took inspiration from similar Christmas attacks in Europe.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Location of bombing2. Pipe bomb attached to suspect with velcro and zip ties, detonated at 7:20 a.m.3. Pipe bomb ignited using christmas light bulb, matches, 9 volt battery, did not detonate properly4. Suspect, others injuredVOICEOVER (in English): "The incident occurred in the underground passageway between the Port Authority Times Square subway stations.""27-year-old suspect Akayed Ullah had strapped a pipe bomb to his body using velcro and zip ties, and detonated the device around 7:20 a.m.""The powder-filled pipe was ignited using a Christmas light bulb, matches, and a 9-volt battery, but failed to detonate properly. One cap was blown off, but the rest of the pipe remained intact.""Ullah sustained burns and lacerations to his hands and abdomen, while several others received minor injuries."SOURCES: New York Times, Reuters, The Telegraphhttps://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/12/11/nyregion/port-authority-explosion-bombing.html?action=click&module=TopStories&pgtype=Homepagehttps://www.reuters.com/article/us-newyork-incident/subway-bomber-wounds-self-three-victims-in-new-york-idUSKBN1E51E9http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/12/11/new-york-police-respond-reports-explosion-inmanhattan/***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
